        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:56AM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 956 AM EDT/856 AM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles southwest of Signal
Mountain to Lookout Mountain to near Trenton. Movement was northeast
at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, East Brainerd, Lookout Mountain, North Chickamauga Creek
Gorge, Fairmount, Lakesite, East Ridge, Ooltewah, Harrison, and
Soddy-Daisy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
